products.name: Bakso
products.description: Bakso is savory meatball and noodle soup. Also has hard boiled eggs and other potential add-ins like tofu or bok choy.

products.name: Mi Goreng
products.description: Mi goreng is a stir-fried noodle dish with a thick and flavorful sauce. You can pick your choice of chicken, beef, shrimp, or all three.

products.name: Nasi Goreng
products.description: Nasi goreng is Indonesia's version of fried rice. Packs more flavor you can pick your choice of chicken, beef, shrimp, or all three. Topped with a fried egg.

products.name: Satay Ayam
products.description: Satay ayam is a chicken skewer marinated in sweet soy sauce and grilled over a flame. Served with a spicy peanut sauce.

products.name: Soto
products.description: Soto is an Indonesian chicken soup with a nice herbal broth and rice noodles, chicken, hard boiled eggs, and other various toppings.

products.name: Martabak Telur
products.description: Martabak telur is a savory roti-like fried pancake stuffed with a beef and egg filling. Very popular on the streets of Indonesia.

products.name: Chicken Kebab
products.description: Chicken kebabs are cubes of chicken marinated in a blend of herbs and spices, skewered, then grilled.

products.name: Falafel
products.description: Falafel is a deep fried ball of chickpeas and other herbs and spices.

products.name: Shakshuka
products.description: Shakshuka is a dish with poached eggs in a tomato based sauce. Served with pita bread.

products.name: Pilaf
products.description: Pilaf is a rice dish where the rice is cooked in a stock or a broth along with other aromatics.

products.name: Baklava
products.description: Baklava is a pastry made with filo dough filled with nuts and held together with honey.

products.name: Hummus with Vegetables
products.description: Hummus is a chickpea paste along with other flavorings, served with vegetables to dip it in.
